Template: openvas/enable_redis
Type: boolean
Default: true
_Description: Do you want to enable redis unix socket in /etc/redis/redis.conf?
 Greenbone vulnerability scanner require redis database to store
 data. It will connect to the database with a unix socket at
 /run/redis/redis.sock.
 .
 If you agree, the installation process will enable redis unix socket
 at this address automatically, by updateing
 /etc/redis/redis.conf. Also the default "databases" value may be
 updated.
 .
 Otherwise, you have to manually update your /etc/redis/redis.conf. An
 example redis configuration provided by GVM developers is available
 at /etc/openvas/redis.conf.example.
